      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a draft email that balances professionalism with kindness:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were impressed by your technical skills and the time you took to showcase your expertise during the interview process. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience in distributed systems aligns more closely with our team's current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were truly impressed by your qualifications and potential. We appreciate the effort you put into preparing for the interview process and the time you invested in our company.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best of luck in your job search. We're confident that your skills will be valuable in your next opportunity, and we hope you'll consider us again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nThis email aims to convey a sense of appreciation for Marcus's qualifications while still being clear about the decision to move forward with another candidate. The tone is professional and kind, but firm, which should help maintain a positive relationship with the candidate.",
